"content": "<style>\nh1.thlex-title { font-size: 1.3em; margin: 0 0 0.4em; }\n.thlex-key { color: #888; font-size: 0.85em; font-weight: normal; margin-right: 0.4em; }\nnav.thlex-index { margin: 0.5em 0 0.75em; }\nnav.thlex-index ul { margin: 0; padding-left: 1.2em; }\nnav.thlex-index li { margin: 0.15em 0; font-size: 0.95em; }\n.thlex-section { margin: 0.6em 0; }\nh2.thlex-heading { font-size: 1em; margin: 0.5em 0 0.2em; }\nh3.thlex-subheading { font-size: 0.95em; font-weight: normal; font-style: italic; margin: 0.2em 0; }\n.thlex-language-sets { margin: 0.3em 0 0.3em 1em; }\n.thlex-language-set { margin: 0.4em 0; padding-left: 0.75em; border-left: 3px solid #e0e0e0; }\n.thlex-language { font-size: 0.8em; color: #888; margin-right: 0.4em; }\n.thlex-lemma { font-weight: bold; font-family: serif; }\n.thlex-translit { color: #555; font-style: italic; font-size: 0.9em; margin-left: 0.3em; }\n.thlex-refs { font-size: 0.85em; color: #444; margin-top: 0.15em; }\n.thlex-paragraphs p { margin: 0.35em 0; font-size: 0.95em; line-height: 1.5; }\n.thlex-image { margin: 0.5em 0; display: block; }\n.thlex-image img { max-width: 100%; height: auto; display: block; }\nfigcaption.thlex-caption { font-size: 0.85em; color: #555; font-style: italic; margin-top: 0.2em; }\n.thlex-abbr { border-bottom: 1px dotted #888; cursor: help; }\n.thlex-xref { color: #1a5fb4; }\nspan[data-bnType=\"bibleReference\"] { color: #1a5fb4; }\ntable.thlex-table { border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 0.9em; margin: 0.5em 0; }\ntable.thlex-table td { padding: 0.2em 0.6em; vertical-align: top; border: 1px solid #ddd; }\ntable.thlex-table tr:first-child td { font-weight: bold; background: #f5f5f5; }\nul.thlex-index-list { margin: 0.4em 0; padding-left: 1.4em; font-size: 0.95em; line-height: 1.6; }\nul.thlex-index-list ul { margin: 0.1em 0; padding-left: 1.4em; }\n.thlex-index-key { font-weight: bold; font-style: italic; }\n</style><h1 class=\"thlex-title\" id=\"REALIA:4.5.6\"><span class=\"thlex-key\">4.5.6</span> 標題：腰帶（sash, cloth belt）</h1><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">經文出處</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-sets\">\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Hebrew</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">來： אַבְנֵט</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(音譯： ’avnet)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod28:4\">EXO 28:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod28:39\">EXO 28:39</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod28:40\">EXO 28:40</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod29:9\">EXO 29:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod39:29\">EXO 39:29</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev8:7\">LEV 8:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev8:13\">LEV 8:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev16:4\">LEV 16:4</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Hebrew</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">來： חגר</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(音譯： chagar)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod29:9\">EXO 29:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev8:7\">LEV 8:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev8:7\">LEV 8:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev8:13\">LEV 8:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev16:4\">LEV 16:4</a></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">描述</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-paragraphs\">\n<p>腰帶是一條長布帶，大祭司把它圍著腰部纏繞幾圈，以扎緊內袍（參<a class=\"thlex-xref\" data-bnType=\"lexiconLink\" data-collection=\"\" data-key=\"\" href=\"#\">4.5.2 內袍、束腰長襯衫、襯衫 (tunic, shirt)&lt;REALIA:4.5.2&gt;</a> ）。其他祭司也束腰帶。<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod39:29\">EXO 39:29</a> 記載，大祭司的腰帶是用四種線以刺繡的手藝做成的。根據後聖經時期的猶太傳統，腰帶長32肘（約16米或53英呎）。即使這個傳統說法有所誇大，腰帶的長度也應該足以纏繞腰部幾圈，然後打結扎緊。參<a class=\"thlex-xref\" data-bnType=\"lexiconLink\" data-collection=\"\" data-key=\"\" href=\"#\">4.5.4 以弗得 (ephod)&lt;REALIA:4.5.4&gt;</a> 中的插圖。</p>\n<hr/>\n</div>\n</div><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">翻譯</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-paragraphs\">\n<p>\n            <abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Revised Standard Version (1952)\">RSV</abbr> 把大祭司繫的這條腰帶譯作“girdle”（「婦女緊身褡」、「腰帶」），在現代英文中，這個詞可能會誤導讀者。這條帶有刺繡的長腰帶除了纏在腰部這個基本用途之外，似乎還有一個象徵意義，就是標誌著祭司的身份。許多英文譯本使用了“sash”（「腰帶」）一詞，但一些語言可能需要譯作「寬帶子」。在<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev8:7\">LEV 8:7</a> ，要注意區分這條腰帶與這節經文稍後提到的「巧工織的以弗得帶子」（<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Revised Standard Version (1952)\">RSV</abbr> 直譯；<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Good News Translation (1992)\">GNT</abbr> 直譯為「精織的腰帶」；參<a class=\"thlex-xref\" data-bnType=\"lexiconLink\" data-collection=\"\" data-key=\"\" href=\"#\">4.5.4 以弗得 (ephod)&lt;REALIA:4.5.4&gt;</a> ）。</p>\n<p>另參<a class=\"thlex-xref\" data-bnType=\"lexiconLink\" data-collection=\"\" data-key=\"\" href=\"#\">6.6 腰帶、皮帶 (waistband, sash, belt)&lt;REALIA:6.6&gt;</a> 中的討論。</p>\n</div>\n</div>",
